  "slug": "codex-guardrails-and-troubleshooting",
  "title": "Guardrails and Troubleshooting",
  "description": "The most common rules and debugging paths when using Codex with the Anydocs MCP server.",
  "tags": [
    "reference",
    "troubleshooting"
  ],
  "status": "published",
  "updatedAt": "2026-04-02T00:00:00.000Z",
  "content": {
    "version": 1,
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "id": "block-1",
        "level": 1,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Guardrails and Troubleshooting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "block-2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common rules to remember:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "id": "block-3",
        "style": "bulleted",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "element-3-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "always pass `projectRoot`"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-4-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "`lang` must be enabled in the project"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-5-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "`page_update` cannot change `status`"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-6-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "`metadata` requires a selected template and must match that template's `metadataSchema`"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-7-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "publishing may be rejected if page approval rules are not satisfied"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-8-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "the full workflow now lives in `anydocs://authoring/guidance`, not in a long root guide file"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "block-9",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When something fails:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "id": "block-10",
        "style": "numbered",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "element-10-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "keep the original error, especially its `rule` and `remediation`"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-11-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "go back to `project_open` or `project_validate`"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-12-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "use `page_get` or `page_find` to confirm the target page really exists"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-13-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "re-check the template definition if the failure is about metadata"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-14-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "do not bypass MCP by editing raw JSON just to get unstuck quickly"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "block-15",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "If those rules are respected, Codex stays much more predictable in daily authoring work."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
